N:ralphmode
D:[ralphmode] Configure Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Gemini CLI for ralph/omg automation with fewer approval prompts while keeping repo boundaries, secret denylists, sandbox-first YOLO rules, and checkpoint behavior explicit.
G:ralph permissions automation claude-code codex-cli gemini-cli sandbox bypass trusted-folders denylist omg

U[5]:
  When approval popups break flow while repeatedly running ralph or omg
  When you need to align Claude Code, Codex CLI, and Gemini CLI settings for the same repo
  When you must separate repo-scoped automation from true YOLO mode
  When expanding automation while keeping guardrails for .env/secrets/destructive shell commands
  When you need to summarize current approval-policy, sandbox, or checkpoint differences by platform

S[6]{n,action,details}:
  1,Define-Boundary,Lock down the project root and denylist (.env secrets rm -rf sudo) first
  2,Choose-Profile,Choose: Claude acceptEdits or bypassPermissions; Codex approval_policy+sandbox_mode; Gemini Trusted Folder or --yolo for disposable sandboxes
  3,Apply-Local,Apply only to project-local settings when possible; limit global defaults to sandbox-only
  4,Run-Ralph,Run in order: boundary check -> permission profile -> ralph or omg -> verify
  5,Separate-Modes,Keep repo automation and sandbox YOLO as different defaults rather than one shared bypass profile
  6,Checkpoints,For Tier 1 actions (.env secrets force-push destructive DB or shell) require approval_policy guardrails or CHECKPOINT_NEEDED before proceeding

R[4]:
  For detailed templates, read only the required sections per platform in references/permission-profiles.md
  For Codex sandbox runs use: codex -c model_reasoning_effort="high" --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox -c model_reasoning_summary="detailed" -c model_supports_reasoning_summaries=true
  Gemini now supports --yolo flag for sandbox YOLO mode (combines sandbox + auto-approve); use only in disposable environments
  Use full bypass only in a disposable sandbox and never as the default for day-to-day repo work

E[4]{desc,in,out}:
  "Claude sandbox preset","claude --dangerously-skip-permissions in disposable sandbox","Fully bypasses approval prompts; combine with repo boundary and denylist"
  "Codex CLI sandbox flags","codex -c model_reasoning_effort=high --dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox -c model_reasoning_summary=detailed -c model_supports_reasoning_summaries=true","Bypasses sandbox and approvals with high-reasoning mode; use only in disposable environments"
  "Gemini YOLO mode","gemini --yolo","Combines sandbox + auto-approve for disposable-sandbox ralph runs"
  "Gemini trust-only","Trust only the repo root folder","Fewer approvals when re-entering the same folder"
